  "text": "Eight multiparous Holstein dairy cows from the University of Illinois Dairy Cattle Research Unit were used. Percutaneous biopsies were obtained at 230 (22863 days; n = 7), 215 (21363 days; n = 8), 1 (n = 8), 15 (n = 8), 30 (n = 8), 60 (n = 6), 120 (n = 6), 240 (n = 5) and 300 (n = 5) days relative to parturition (d) as previously described [CITATION_1] .",
